HEADWORD: Glout
<hw>Glout</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To view attentively;
to gloat on; to stare at.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

